------------------------------------------------------------------------
r6783 | josef | 2005-01-21 11:49:07 +0100 (Fr, 21 Jan 2005) | 6 lines
Geänderte Pfade:
   M /trunk/libggz/src/security/ggz_tls_gnutls.c

- sleep() one second in client before doing the handshake

I think there's a bug in ggzd in that it tries to read TLS data
even when it shouldn't (while doing handshake). Using sleep() is a quick hack
but seems to work.

