------------------------------------------------------------------------
r4545 | jdorje | 2002-09-13 17:43:04 +0200 (Fr, 13 Sep 2002) | 11 lines
Geänderte Pfade:
   M /trunk/libggz/src/msg.c

To help in debugging: ggz_error_msg_exit and ggz_error_sys_exit abort(),
instead of just exiting.  ggz_error_msg and ggz_error_sys fork and abort,
to leave core while the original process continues.

If core is disabled "ulimit -c 0", no core will be left and the behavior
will be virtually unchanged (at least on my platform).

Eventually something slightly more complicated may be better: we can
attach the core to gdb (if it exists) and mail a backtrace to ggz-dev.
THere's probably some tool out there for automating this.

------------------------------------------------------------------------
r4507 | jdorje | 2002-09-11 05:37:21 +0200 (Mi, 11 Sep 2002) | 2 lines
Geänderte Pfade:
   M /trunk/libggz/src/ggz_common.h
   M /trunk/libggz/src/numberlist.c
   M /trunk/libggz/tests/ggzcommon.c

